messages.content: How did the minecraft movie do on its opening weekend? Have the reviews been good?

As of July 4, 2025, "A Minecraft Movie," which was released on April 4, 2025, had a successful opening weekend, grossing $162.75 million in North America from 4,263 theaters [boxofficereport](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGY5WfjI2M9QvSwEr7ecD3ocBzN4zgXSW0_y9IYPVAuwpkyMtZ6yn6Yz5Y8msYfvEZGT27qlVLTmnuYliyxrSsBHztKw_cfdNisD2h1YPmLBxi7diUhqqR3KBQZZjpMIok1a5WMJJTqxNHvcGA3s5UxiY3-A4Aecb0JrodUKWs=) [the-numbers](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEjLUZ_tREzsM0uZy6fnnIhM31gnP6kMJ7PTSTEOpxzZLDvXQbp-CWEqkOidey5Mrg7QTLiav5txW6LsVMX8rdLHYiftFstzUGqHr9dMnwtkVLzEd70j8zVUXnTIvHLJs8AIvKXrj-dAKMPAr89bPXDcEYcHvQ=). Globally, its debut reached $313.7 million [screendaily](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHuqcGwKTRea4q6yzx4j8nw_TdF0k7rC037ubVxw18UK5Lkm2wOH4sEYy0gCKa5eUi_CFaSTWk487JVjaThobhSyZUXNr6DoclvaPOj4wnfpdYNcar7K2rloyefjx1S5UeyoD21djt363Ili8d5m0kNaC3UeUQKZkMv4lfipg_X3PUbEhIkLa36s66pJiZdc3n65WPm9faD). The film has grossed $954.9 million worldwide [wdwnt](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF8_z9nMluB5BCwLiGXMEHrKNYDVMqsHJSrsEgKibCTgZPag17hdObHOQVkXG6JhYvU-b64Chs3UhJatw39S6z3G7nhTMFygPI5Sf7iFndpl1BpSV4mQslnSmuJsATkvRqQxTCWjg6muGA1Klc6OcxclJm3FarWyVcGc3ytJfoLBV-2QGsoekfsjDd6TYPtY6GVoLs5hV_ddsKywQi7WPHpGLtbwEnqnEGr3ZGhOuGiB_g=].

Reviews for "A Minecraft Movie" have been mixed [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE8XD56e2c7JM7RrADjaOaoXb4Tcw5yK9U1Udh5E1-YpUYu7QZjlJVz-hDi78LXoenMI7dDUxaKVYPTuFR5CNvF0oFZ4l-yarcwSNLR_DHl4_NEqbU8wjfJLK2GqLaEjXhlE7qvqBYUa1jS). Rotten Tomatoes gives the film a 48% positive rating, summarizing the critical consensus as: "Ostensibly a film about celebrating creativity, A Minecraft Movie provides a colorful sandbox for Jack Black and Jason Momoa to amusingly romp around in a story curiously constructed from conventional building blocks" [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE8XD56e2c7JM7RrADjaOaoXb4Tcw5yK9U1Udh5E1-YpUYu7QZjlJVz-hDi78LXoenMI7dDUxaKVYPTuFR5CNvF0oFZ4l-yarcwSNLR_DHl4_NEqbU8wjfJLK2GqLaEjXhlE7qvqBYUa1jS). Metacritic assigned the film a score of 45 out of 100, based on 40 critics, indicating "mixed or average" reviews [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQE8XD56e2c7JM7RrADjaOaoXb4Tcw5yK9U1Udh5E1-YpUYu7QZjlJVz-hDi78LXoenMI7dDUxaKVYPTuFR5CNvF0oFZ4l-yarcwSNLR_DHl4_NEqbU8wjfJLK2GqLaEjXhlE7qvqBYUa1jS) [metacritic](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFR6lMwZzh8NNFBeQ5LsR1yylrHBXUJ1Ie_mm7JXRDRzPTvbrAKE4SoCfZXZ9wGPyhIQMNEM2GoQ92fb8vh6qCSlsGf1q76Bvr5amlrsvESCbfeYpaEjmyHCd45mfroXyHP4SMAD8_P_269qRVpyA==). Despite the mixed critical reception, the film has an impressive 83% audience score on Rotten Tomatoes, indicating a strong positive reception from viewers [thenerdnet](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG8km8QsrXIatGbVIMrEe1hu2KzwWRR1EZytP9Ey-K4GXJWr2jQ0QWIh72ofuy-xiPYxst6XMrwPe22M5lZbKgUViWqSJoiMMlRAKl63lURC9WXe9jfp7ZFQoqtcmwBYWKjHN73RphRIRHxW2MuxVSRbKmAQsRHuw8bVYipWaJmpkE2mtE2kAglFe50n5cvSg==].

Okay, here's a summary of "Minecraft Movie" reviews as of July 4, 2025, based on the search results:

**General Reception:**

*   "A Minecraft Movie" received mixed reviews from critics [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).
*   However, it was a box-office success, grossing $955 million worldwide against a $150 million budget, becoming the second-highest-grossing film of 2025 and the second-highest-grossing video game film of all time [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).
*   As of June 30, 2025, the film grossed $424 million in the United States and Canada, and $531 million in other territories [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).
*   The film has an impressive 83% audience score on Rotten Tomatoes, indicating a strong positive reception from viewers [thenerdnet](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).

**Critical Consensus:**

*   Rotten Tomatoes gives the film a 48% positive rating, with the consensus: "Ostensibly a film about celebrating creativity, A Minecraft Movie provides a colorful sandbox for Jack Black and Jason Momoa to amusingly romp around in a story curiously constructed from conventional building blocks" [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).
*   Metacritic assigned the film a score of 45 out of 100, based on 40 critics, indicating "mixed or average" reviews [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0) [metacritic](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-2).

**Positive Aspects:**

*   Many critics acknowledge that "A Minecraft Movie" works for its young target audience, and maybe even for some of their parents [rottentomatoes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   Committed performances from Jack Black, Jason Momoa, and Jennifer Coolidge are frequently cited as enjoyable [rottentomatoes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   Some reviewers found the film fun, silly, and wholesome [goatfilmreviews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [rottentomatoes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   The film's humor was appreciated by some, with some finding it surprisingly funny [headphonesthoughts](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [rottentomatoes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   The movie has a message to creatives to maybe sometimes turn off the game and go out into the world to build something [goatfilmreviews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4).
*   Some appreciate the film's faithfulness to the game's aesthetic [thenerdnet](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-1).

**Negative Aspects:**

*   Some critics found the writing fairly standard and generic [rottentomatoes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   Some felt the film could have been more imaginative and original [rottentomatoes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   A common complaint was a simplistic and generic storyline [goatfilmreviews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4).
*   Some reviews mention bland cinematography and an unfunny script [purexbox](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6).
*   Some critics felt the film was uninspired and unimaginative [ricethresher](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).
*   Some found the visual effects remarkably ugly, eschewing the original game's sublime simplicity [ricethresher](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7).
*   The film's pacing suffers in the middle act [headphonesthoughts](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [themovieblog](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8).

**Key Actors and Characters:**

*   Jack Black and Jason Momoa's comedic performances are frequently highlighted [goatfilmreviews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [purexbox](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6) [rottentomatoes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [dailycampus](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-9).
*   Jennifer Coolidge's role, while minor, was found humorous by some [goatfilmreviews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [udreview](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10).
*   The character of Steve (played by Jack Black) is mentioned in several reviews [headphonesthoughts](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [rogerebert](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-11) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).

**Themes and Messages:**

*   The film touches on themes of creativity, self-expression, family, and connection [headphonesthoughts](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5) [themovieblog](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-8) [goatfilmreviews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [udreview](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-10).
*   A central message is that you don't have to limit your creativity to video games and can be creative in the real world [headphonesthoughts](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-5).

**Audience Reactions:**

*   The film has sparked boisterous reactions and disorderly conduct from viewers, particularly adolescent boys, with some participating in a viral Internet phenomenon on TikTok, alongside other social media platforms [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-0).
*   Some cinemas experienced trashing due to audiences losing control during a scene involving a "zombie boy rides a chicken" [moviemeisterreviews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-12).

**Comparisons to Other Works:**

*   Some reviews compare the film to other video game adaptations like "The Super Mario Bros. Movie" and "Dungeons & Dragons: Honor Among Thieves" [rottentomatoes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3).
*   Some compare the film's humor to Jared Hess's previous works like "Napoleon Dynamite" [goatfilmreviews](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-4) [ricethresher](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-7) [purexbox](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6).
*   The film is also compared to "The Lego Movie" and "Jumanji" [rottentomatoes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-3) [purexbox](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/1-6).

In summary, "A Minecraft Movie" appears to be a commercially successful, but critically divisive film. While it may appeal to younger audiences and fans of the game, some critics found it to be unoriginal and lacking in narrative depth. The performances of Jack Black and Jason Momoa were generally well-received, and the film touches on themes of creativity and self-expression.
